# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# .env.example (repo root) — frontend build / deploy environment
# Copy to .env for local overrides. NEVER commit the real .env.
#
# The API server has its OWN env file with the full set of server vars
# (DATABASE_URL, JWT_SECRET, ADMIN_*, CORS_ORIGIN, SMTP_*, etc.):
#   → see server/.env.example
# This root file only holds build/deploy-time variables for the Vite frontend.
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── App base URL ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Canonical public base URL of the deployed app (frontend origin). The API server
# (server/index.js) reads this as the CORS_ORIGIN fallback AND to build the invite
# and password-reset links it emails (e.g. ${APP_BASE_URL}/reset?token=…). In
# production set to the HTTPS origin, e.g. https://pecanrev.com.
# (Full email/SMTP config lives in server/.env — see server/.env.example.)
APP_BASE_URL="http://localhost:3000"

# ── Vite (frontend) ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Only variables prefixed VITE_ are exposed to the client bundle at build time.
# The frontend currently calls the API via the relative /api path (proxied in
# dev by vite.config.js to 127.0.0.1:3001), so no VITE_ vars are required today.
# Add them here as they are introduced, e.g.:
# VITE_API_BASE_URL="/api"
